Prisoner's Defence. A woman lodged with me; I was told she had bad money, and informed Furzeman's brother. She heard of it, and said she would get a man for 5 s. to put me where I wanted to put her. I could not get rid of her. I was selling vegatables in the street; my little boy came and said a man wanted me, and he had seen him give (
